      "job_title": "Senior Manager - IT Risk Management",
      "job_apply_link": "https://in.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a5531095ed83a9d4",
      "job_description": "With a startup spirit and 90,000+ curious and courageous minds, we have the expertise to go deep with the world’s biggest brands—and we have fun doing it! We dream in digital, dare in reality, and reinvent the ways companies work to make an impact far bigger than just our bottom line. We’re harnessing the power of technology and humanity to create meaningful transformation that moves us forward in our pursuit of a world that works better for people.\n\nNow, we’re calling upon the thinkers and doers, those with a natural curiosity and a hunger to keep learning, keep growing. People who thrive on fearlessly experimenting, seizing opportunities, and pushing boundaries to turn our vision into reality. And as you help us create a better world, we will help you build your own intellectual firepower.\n\nWelcome to the relentless pursuit of better.\n\nInviting applications for the role of Senior Manager, IT Risk Management!\n\nWe are seeking a highly experienced and knowledgeable Senior Manager to join our consulting team and manage the Third-Party Risk Management (TPRM) Assessment, TPRM Platform Implementation, Cyber Security CoE, and Controls in Digital functions for our clients. As a Senior Manager, you will provide strategic guidance, subject matter expertise, and thought leadership to our clients to help them manage and mitigate cyber risks.\n\nThe ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of the latest trends and developments in the field of cybersecurity, particularly in TPRM, and will be able to translate this knowledge into effective solutions for our clients. You will manage a team of professionals and work closely with our clients to deliver exceptional services in the following areas:\n\nResponsibilities\n• Develop and execute the TPRM Infosec Assessment strategy for clients, including identifying, assessing, and mitigating third-party cybersecurity risks. This includes reviewing and analysing third-party risk assessments, developing risk mitigation plans, and communicating risks and mitigation strategies to clients.\n• Implement and manage the TPRM platform for clients, including the development of workflows, process maps, and controls to ensure compliance with internal and external policies and regulations. This includes configuring the platform to meet clients' needs, performing data analysis and reporting, and providing training and support to clients.\n• Develop and maintain the Cyber Security Center of Excellence (CoE) for clients to provide subject matter expertise in cyber risk management, threat intelligence, and incident management, technology risk management. This includes developing and implementing cybersecurity policies and procedures, testing controls, providing training and awareness to clients, and responding to cybersecurity incidents.\n• Manage the Controls in Digital function for clients, including developing, implementing, and monitoring controls to protect their digital assets and ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and industry standards. This includes conducting assessments, developing remediation plans, and providing guidance on best practices for cybersecurity controls.\n• Partner with clients across the organization to build strong relationships and ensure effective collaboration in managing cyber risks. This includes working with senior leadership to develop risk management strategies, communicating with stakeholders to assess risk and prioritize activities, and managing client expectations and concerns.\n• Work with the senior leadership team to develop and execute a roadmap for the TPRM, Cyber Security CoE, and Controls in Digital functions for clients. This includes identifying opportunities for growth and improvement, developing business cases for new services or capabilities, and tracking progress against goals and objectives.\n• Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and developments in TPRM, cyber risk management, and related areas to provide thought leadership and strategic guidance to clients. This includes conducting research, attending conferences and seminars, and participating in professional organizations.\n\nQualifications we seek in you!\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n• Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Information Security, or related field.\n• Relevant experience in TPRM, cyber risk management, or related areas, with at least 5 years of experience in a consulting role.\n• Strong knowledge of TPRM, cyber risk management, and related frameworks and standards such as ISO, NIST, and CSA.\n• Experience in managing complex projects and leading teams in a consulting environment. This includes project planning, scoping, and resource allocation, as well as managing project budgets and timelines.\n• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to build strong relationships with clients and colleagues. This includes listening actively, communicating effectively, and presenting complex information in a clear and concise manner.\n• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to identify and evaluate potential cybersecurity risks and develop effective risk mitigation strategies.\n• Experience with TPRM platforms and tools, such as OneTrust, ProcessUnity, ServiceNow, or other similar platforms.\n• Knowledge of digital controls and cybersecurity frameworks, such as COBIT, COSO, or ITIL.\n• Experience in managing and mentoring teams, including recruiting, training, and developing team members.\n• Professional certifications such as CISM, CISSP, CISA, or similar are preferred.\n\nGenpact is an Equal Opportunity Employer and considers applicants for all positions without regard to race, color, religion or belief, sex, age, national origin, citizenship status, marital status, military/veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, physical or mental disability or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws. Genpact is committed to creating a dynamic work environment that values diversity and inclusion, respect and integrity, customer focus, and innovation. For more information, visit www.genpact.com . Follow us on Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn, and YouTube.\n\nJobSenior Manager\n\nPrimary LocationIndia-Mumbai\n\nEducation LevelMaster's / Equivalent\n\nJob PostingMar 14, 2023, 7:48:49 AM\n\nUnposting DateOngoing\n\nMaster Skills ListConsulting\n\nJob CategoryFull Time",
