      "job_apply_link": "https://startup.jobs/senior-manager-taxation-zeta-4218666",
      "job_description": "About Zeta\n\nZeta is a Next-Gen Banking Tech company that empowers banks and fintechs to launch banking products for the future. It was founded by Bhavin Turakhia and Ramki Gaddipati in 2015. Please read Zeta’s Manifesto here.\n\nZeta’s omni stack for banks is the industry’s first modern, cloud-native, and fully API-enabled stack that brings together acquiring, issuance, processing, lending, core banking, fraud & risk, and many more capabilities as a single-vendor stack. 15M+ cards have been issued on our platform globally.\n\nZeta has over 1700+ employees - with over 70% in technology roles - across locations in the US, EMEA, and Asia. We raised $280 million at a $1.5 billion valuation from Softbank, Mastercard, and other investors in 2021.\n\nLearn more @ www.zeta.tech, careers.zeta.tech, Linkedin, Twitter, Press Room\n\nAbout the Role\nWe are looking for an experienced professional for the position of Senior Manager Taxation, who can work very closely with the CFO and senior management to manage the multiple operations of the tax practice area and to provide with innovative tax planning and reviewing of complex international transactions from tax perspective.\nWhat is the job like?\n\n• Handling the tax compliance and strategy across group entities globally\n• M&A and cross border structuring\n• Global Transfer Pricing\n• Reviewing transactions across all group entities to ensure minimum tax leakages\n• To review the international transactions keeping into perspective the local laws and Double taxation Avoidance agreements\n• To work on a wide variety of complex, demanding and high profile transactions related to fundraising, acquisitions, mergers, buy-outs, and joint ventures.\n• Provide innovative tax structures to optimize the desired commercial objectives\n• Oversight of the tax returns for the Company's international subsidiaries.\n• Handling the tax strategy and compliance with respect to the overseas group companies\n• Handling of the international Litigations and providing reports to the management.\n• Handling GST across all group entities in India\n\nWho should apply to this role?\n\n•\nFunctional Competencies\n• Must be a Qualified Chartered Accountant\n• Post-qualification work experience of atleast 8 years with specialization in International taxation\nBehavioral Competencies\n• Likes working in a challenging and fast paced environment\n• lead and cultivate high performing team\n• Ideate and produce creative content\n• Design and document policies\n• Strong analytical, logical and numerical aptitude\n• Strong process orientation\n• Listen actively and connect with individuals in the organization\n\nLife At Zeta\nAt Zeta, we want you to grow to be the best version of yourself by unlocking the great potential that lies within you. This is why our core philosophy is ‘People Must Grow.’ We recognize your aspirations; act as enablers by bringing you the right opportunities, and let you grow as you chase disruptive goals.\n\n#LifeAtZeta is adventurous and exhilarating at the same time. You get to work with some of the best minds in the industry and experience a culture that values the diversity of thoughts. If you want to push boundaries, learn continuously and grow to be the best version of yourself, Zeta is the place to be! Explore the life at zeta\n\nZeta is an equal opportunity employer\n\nAt Zeta, we are committed to equal employment opportunities regardless of job history, disability, gender identity, religion, race, marital/parental status, or other special status. We are proud to be an equitable workplace that welcomes individuals from all walks of life if they fit the roles and responsibilities.",
