      "job_apply_link": "https://www.glassdoor.co.in/job-listing/senior-manager-partnerships-and-fundraising-india-health-fund-JV_IC2851180_KO0,43_KE44,61.htm?jl=1008529731766",
      "job_description": "If you are interested in joining the fight against infectious diseases through science- and tech-led innovations, we want to hear from you. Please highlight how you can contribute and send your CV at CHATFHR@indiahealthfund.org\n\nSenior Manager - Partnerships & Fundraising\n\nJob Description: Senior Manager - Partnerships & Fundraising\n\nAbout us\n\nIndia Health Fund (IHF) is a collaborative initiative of the Tata Trusts and The Global Fund to leverage the power of collective impact and catalyse India’s fight against infectious diseases. IHF was conceived to accelerate India’s progress towards the elimination of infectious diseases in line with the objectives of the Government of India and UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), by supporting the development of breakthrough solutions which help accelerate eradication of these diseases as well as aggregate funds and deploy resources to finance the development of these solutions to enable better outcomes in diagnosis, treatment, control and monitoring of infectious diseases. Key collaborators of the IHF include central and state government agencies, philanthropists, civil society organisations, incubators, start-ups, knowledge institutions, technical partners, business leaders, corporations.\n\nResponsibilities\n• Lead development of strategy, development, and execution of relevant partnerships and implementation initiatives\n• Shall be responsible for leading the development and implementation of fundraising, public engagement, and associated marketing strategies for the organization.\n• Strategy to expand partnerships with external stakeholders, both domestically and internationally, and forge partnerships that contribute not only to encouraging greater philanthropic capital to social issues but also promotes knowledge, partnerships with external stakeholders, development of technology platforms, research, and advocacy.\n• Lead cross-functional implementation coordination & activities for specified projects or partnerships\n• Develop, implement & manage cross-functional projects & initiatives\n• Develop & manage relationships with identified external stakeholders\n• Lead assessment & selection of partnership opportunities\n• Develop rolling & annual work plans for focus area & team\n• Budgeting & forecasting for projects & other initiatives aligned with the rolling work plan\n\nSkills Required\n• Lead direct reports, external stakeholders, and cross-functional colleagues in strategy development & execution\n• Business planning & forecasting\n• Financial literacy: P&L management, cash flow, cost accounting, pricing\n• Team management, Coaching\n• Ability to work independently, seek guidance & support where required\n• Conceptualisation\n• Strong strategic fundraising leadership skills\n• Ability to understand the programs and proposal development\n• Negotiation and persuasive ability with a collaborative mindset\n\nExperience\n• Track record in leading partnerships or strategy in a consulting firm, impact investment fund, social sector or grant organization, start-up, or social enterprise.\n• Experience in strategy, fundraising, operations, or partnerships team at an impact investment fund, social sector, or grant organization\n• Must have 8-10 years of experience in resource mobilization, of which 7-8 years should have been in successfully designing and implementing fundraising strategies for non-profit organizations, section-8 Companies. (Experience in fundraising for Public Health section 8 Companies will be an added advantage).\n• >2 years experience in leading teams of 3 or more people\n• Established relationships with stakeholders relevant to the role\n• Experience in healthcare and/or public health is desirable\n\nJob location\n\nMumbai",
