      "job_description": "Director/Senior Manager - Training US Healthcare with GeBBS Healthcare Solutions\n\nDepartment : Accounts Receivable US Healthcare\n\nReporting to: Vice President\n\nShift: US Shift ( Work from Office)\n\nLocation: Airoli , Navi Mumbai\n\nKey Role :\n\n- Internal & External Stakeholder management\n\n- Heading Training Team of AR vertical\n\n- Migrations / Setup start-up projects\n\n- Planning & Budgeting revenues and controls\n\n- Client Relationship Management\n\n- Process and people related change management\n\nJob Responsibilities :\n\n- Managing and leading the Training team by developing a detailed Training Model.\n\n- Instruction, or facilitation, of various training's as per the requirement such as Process Specific training, Certification training, Continuing education programs, Refresher training etc.\n\n- Assuring that every training is delivered and driven within the area of expertise, and it meets the current standards of the organization and market trend.\n\n- Identify the Skill gap of the training staff has obtained and is maintaining their technical and instructional knowledge and skills.\n\n- Ensure successful learning and talent outcomes by supporting the identification and translation of the client's capability and skill needs into a defined learning and talent strategy with recommended solutions\n\n- Assist the operations in identifying potential training needs based on process and industry requirements.\n\n- Monitors the Trainer's (Process trainer's & Lead trainer's) performance to verify training is conducted as outlined in approved training materials and in a manner that motivates personnel to learn\n\n- Identifying the Training needs across operations and based on the client request develop training plan effective enough to bring process improvement and client satisfaction.\n\n- Identifying the training needs and devising and managing training programmers' according to the approved methodology.\n\n- To act as a Coordinator for the external training programs.\n\n- Work to establish mutual trust and cooperation between the training Team and the Operations.\n\n- Created a standard training approach for all learning initiatives - Training Need Identification, Refresher Training, Knowledge Assessments and Process Documentation\n\n- Develop improved methods by implementing Adult training principles to meet training and facility objectives and goals as required\n\n- Initiate and help prepare long-range objectives for the training organization that are consistent with corporate, facility, and training policies, and develop a system for verifying implementation of the actions needed to meet the objectives\n\nQualification :\n\n- A degree in any field\n\n- Must have trained and managed Training team\n\n- Having experience in US Healthcare RCM Process Training, Soft Skills and Behavioral Training.\n\n- Team handling experience\n\n- 10+ years with Minimum 4+yrs relevant experience in Training in Medical Billing, Accounts Receivable (AR)/ Revenue Cycle Management(RCM)\n\nInterested candidate WhatsApp your profile on +91 9619814875",
