      "job_description": "Senior Manager - Inside & Channel Partner Sales\n\nGroup Company: 91 Springboard Business Hub Private Limited\n\nDesignation: Senior Manager - Inside & Channel Partner Sales\n\nOffice Location: Bengaluru/ Mumbai\n\nPosition description:\n\nLead, manage, monitor, guide the Inside Sales team by creating & manage a very efficient sales process to sell hub seats to smaller ticket customers (generally less than 20 memberships, <500 company size) in a cost effective manner at 91springboard. The role shall be responsible for contributing to approx. 30-35% of monthly new sales revenue (subject to available inventory). Be responsible for creating sales strategy, and drive sales performance at all the hubs with the objective of achieving the Hub FTE targets and oversee the day to day operations of the Inside Sales Team.\n\nNo. of direct reports: 4-6\n\nNo. of indirect reports: 15-20\n\nKey Stakeholder Network:\n\na. Internal\n• Hub Operations Team\n• Presales Team\n• Marketing Team\n• Enterprise Sales\n• Finance & Business Intelligence\n\nb. External\n\nAll prospective clients of 91springboard\n\nEducation Guidelines: MBA - Sales\n\nExperience Guidelines:\n• 7 to 10 years of Sales Experience with at least 4 years of managing inside sales or call based selling team / 2-3 Years\n• Experience of selling to SMB customers is preferred\n• Should have experience in managing pipelines with high incoming leads per month per sales agent\n\nKnowledge & Skills:\n\na. Technical\n• Market Research & Analysis\n• Sales Forecasting & Planning\n• Business / Product Understanding\n• Negotiation Skills\n• Customer Understanding\n• Analytical Skills\n• Skilled in managing through data & looking at reports\n\nb. Behavioural\n• Customer Orientation\n• Collaboration\n• Results Orientation\n• Stakeholder Management\n• Strategic Orientation\n• Decision Making\n• Interpersonal Effectiveness\n• People Management\n\nAreas of Responsibility:\n\na. Strategic & Planning Responsibilities:\n• Design and implement Inside Sales Operating plan in line with the overall sales strategy and drive setting of daily, weekly and monthly targets for the team through the Zonal Team Leads\n• Deliver all Inside sales targets for respective hubs in accordance to the predefined base pricing\n• Design & implement effective sales processes for optimum performance and efficient running of Inside Sales operation\n• Review metrics and reports for tracking progress and performance, allocate resources and identify improvements needed in sales processes\n• Review and take effective timely measures to ensure a healthy sales pipeline with qualified leads across the zones\n• Conduct periodic zone-wise reviews to track target achievement and identify the challenges faced in different hubs with respect to lead quality & quantity, customer preference, etc.\n• Review zonal performance report using CRM data to understand performance, identify the issues/challenges, and work with the concerned team leads to come up with a solution and implement it across the hubs, if required. Proactively identify bottlenecks or anticipated challenges and provide required support to Team Leads to ensure targets for each zone is achieved\n\nb. Control/ Financial Responsibilities:\n• Maintain healthy profits and unit economics by ensuring price is in line with the base pricing\n• Accurately forecast sales for each zone and hub, communicate the same to the stakeholders, monitor sales achievement regularly to ensure minimum deviation\n• Ensure consistency in communication by the zonal teams team to potential customers\n• Build and review controls to ensure the inventory within the approved range and push for higher targeted ASPs across the country\n\nc. Functional Responsibilities:\n• Conduct periodic review and audits to ensure the CRM health and ensure accountability of the same with the zonal Team Leads.\n• Enable and develop the IS team to manage more complex deals and follow a defined Replenishment Process\n• Build insights and market intelligence in coordination with the Market research team and the Marketing team and share the inputs the zonal teams for enabling better objection handling and price pitching.\n• Build insights into the sales funnel by reviewing Stage wise Sales conversion trends of the customer journey and scale up the best practices / ideas across the hubs.\n• Drive initiatives for bringing in operational excellence in the existing methods and build more efficient and effective processes.\n• Partner with Marketing team to drive required leads for Inside Sales Managers at regular intervals\n• Review the Lead quality and volumes periodically with the Zonal Team leads and share feedback with Marketing team to improve the same.\n• Review consolidated reports of member feedback on the hubs, service levels, pricing etc. post hub tours and share the feedback with the immediate superiors and Hub teams for enhancement\n• Periodically review the inside sales pitch/scripts with random call audits for ensuring consistent communications with prospective customer across the zones.\n\nd. People Responsibilities:\n• Manage, guide and mentor teams to promote a high-performance culture\n• Collaborate with HR to identifying, recruiting and engaging high quality talent for Sales Team\n• Set performance objectives, provide necessary support, evaluate/ appraise incumbents and provide regular feedback on performance\n• Learn and share best practices with other team members by participating in knowledge sharing sessions\n\nPrimary Responsibilities:\n\nThe role shall be responsible for contributing to approx. 30-35% of monthly new sales revenue (subject to available inventory).\n\nBe responsible for creating sales strategy & drive sales performance at all the hubs with the objective of achieving the Hub FTE targets and oversee the day to day operations of the Inside Sales Team\n\nReporting Team\n\nReporting Designation: Vice President - Sales\n\nReporting Department: Sales",
