      "job_description": "Network Security and Architect\n\nSenior/Chief Manager Cyber Security (Network Security and Architect)\n\nWhat is expected?\n\n- Lead Network security and architect for Cloud and Datacenter environment\n\n- Responsible for designing, maintaining network security architecture, analyzing network data and systems to ensure appropriate control mechanism is implemented commensurate to the requirement\n\n- Evaluate solutions for IOT/ network/cloud security including FW, Threat & compliance management\n\n- Liaise with managers to promote good security practices and explain security procedures\n\n- Work with external suppliers to source hardware and software solutions to network security issues\n\n- Deploy, test and maintain security systems such as VPNs, firewalls, email security and cloud security\n\n- Access review of all privilege access provide for all devices\n\n- Ensure that current network system security is updated / upgraded and suitable for future requirements\n\n- Define policies and procedures appropriate to the systems and advice users and administrators\n\n- Conduct periodic assessment and have oversight for the security levels specific to the systems\n\n- Ensure tracking and implementation of controls for gaps noted during security assessments\n\n- Monitor compliance with security policies and procedures\n\n- Monitor and review security incident logs for various security incidents and work closely with SOC\n\n- Key member for any cybersecurity incident response team and manage recovery / response end to end\n\n- Coordinate with respective teams to the annual risk assessment and risk-based investigation of controls\n\nFunctional competencies:\n\n- Familiar with best practices / standards / frameworks commonly used like ITIL, ISO 27001, Mitre Attack\n\n- Good knowledge and experience on network security architecture, cloud technologies, information systems security & controls as per standards and best practices\n\n- Knowledge of various standards and risk frameworks on Cloud Security ; CIS, CCM by CSA, etc.\n\nCritical Generic Competencies:\n\n- Independent and proactive approach to work; ability to learn and adapt new areas\n\n- Good written, communication and presentation skills\n\n- Project management skills\n\nQualification & Experience:\n\n- MBA Information Security/ Engineering Graduate with working knowledge in the domain of cyber security and cloud standard.\n\n- Overall experience of 8+ years with relevant experience of at-least 5 years hands-on in the domain of network architecture, network security and cloud security.\n\n- Working knowledge of Networks, cloud security and cyber security framework\n\n- Good understanding of infrastructure components, routers, firewalls, IPS, NAC, Threat Management tools, WIFI, IOT, cloud.\n\nCertifications:\n\n- Product certifications ; Firewall, IPS, NAC, Security tools\n\n- Information Systems Security Architecture Professional (ISSAP), Certified Information Systems\n\n- Security Professional (CISSP), CCSP, CISA, Lead Auditors\n\n- Other certifications like Cloud Service Providers like, AWS, Azure",
