      "job_description": "Company Background:\n\nSUGAR Cosmetics (www.sugarcosmetics.com) is India's fastest-growing premium cosmetics brand with a product portfolio that has consistently received excellent reviews across its own and partner channels. With a cult-following across millennials, SUGAR targets 25 to 35-year- old women with clutter-breaking products that have rich payoff with its unapologetically bold brand identity. The 7-year old company recently secured its Series D funding from L Catterton. to further accelerate and build an exciting global beauty brand. We are now looking for ambitious, driven individuals to join us on this journey and create experiences of a lifetime and our team is currently looking to hire for the role of an Senior Manager - Growth Marketing, DTC role.\n\nWebsite: http://www.sugarcosmetics.com\n\nCompany Size: 700+\n\nAddress: Chromium, WeWork, Jogeshwari - Vikhroli Link Rd, Andheri East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400072\n\nPosition: Senior Manager - Growth Marketing, DTC\n\nSugar Cosmetics raises $50 million led by L Catterton:\n\nhttps://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/funding/sugar-cosmetics-raises-50-million-led-by-l-catterton/articleshow/91898603.cms\n\n1. Consumer Acquisition & Retention through Digital\n\n- Acquisition\n\n- Paid Media\n\n- Search Engine Optimization\n\n- Content\n\n- Retention\n\n- Consumer Segmentation\n\n- Personalized CRM Marketing\n\n- Marketing Automation Platform Management\n\n- Referral Programme\n\n- Loyalty Programme\n\n2. Website & App Asset Management\n\n- Tech Stack Management\n\n- Conversion Rate Optimization\n\n- UI-UX\n\n- COD & RTO reduction\n\n- New Features (Recommendation Engine, Video Commerce etc.)\n\n3. Communication Strategy on DTC\n\n- Creative Strategy for Paid Media\n\n- Promo & Offer Design\n\n- Communication design for post purchase experience, repurchase journeys etc.\n\n4. Product & Pricing Strategy\n\n- New Product / Product Category Launches\n\n- AOV improvement\n\n- Product Combo design\n\n5. Media, Consumer & Business Analytics\n\n- Visit/Install to Purchase Behaviour\n\n- Repeat Purchase Behaviour - Frequency, Time Gaps, Product mix\n\n- Market Basket Analysis\n\n- Price Point & Product category Analysis\n\n6. Alliances & Partnerships\n\n- Co-Branded Promotions with relevant Brands\n\n- Tie-ups with Banks for co-promotion of offers\n\n- Data Partnerships\n\n- Engagement with specific communities\n\n7. Operations\n\n- Inventory Planning & Management\n\n- Dispatch and Delivery Process Efficiency\n\n- Delivery Experience Enhancement for Customers\n\nJob Highlights: Holistic learning across Business P&L, Business Operations & Customer Delight with exposure to Marketing, Product & Technology\n\nPreferred Candidate Profile:\n\n1. Overall experience of around 5 years in marketing, digital & business operations domain\n\n2. Core experience of at least 2 years on digital performance marketing\n\n3. MBA in Marketing preferable but not compulsory\n\n4. Experience in a performance marketing agency is highly preferred\n\n5. Business ownership experience highly preferred.",
