      "job_description": "Leadership Opportunity as Manager/Senior Manager\n\nJob: Responsible for achieving the sales order booking targets, unit sales and collections within budgeted timelines. The role is also responsible for ensuring seamless sales experience for customers.\n\nStrategic :\n\n- Contribute and participate in the formulation and implementation of the sales plan for the project\n\n- Participate in conceptualization & launch of sales initiatives to maximize sales order booking for the project\n\n- Evaluate market trends and competitor activities to protect existing sales and maximize future sales opportunities\n\nOperational :\n\nSales :\n\n- Ensure generation of leads through multiple channels such as Channel Partners, Loyalty & referrals through existing customers, Corporates, Local market activations etc.\n\n- Proactively contact potential customers to promote the project\n\n- Ensure prompt responsiveness on sales enquiries so as to maximize sales conversions\n\n- Coordinate with other functions viz. Customer Care, Project Management Group, Legal on customer queries\n\n- Identify and develop relations with existing & new key customers (E.g. Corporates, HNI Clients)\n\n- Develop relationships with Partners (brokers/ property consultants) to ensure market penetration\n\n- Negotiate and close deals with customers\n\n- Ensure timely collection of payments from customers as per company requirements\n\n- Ensure accurate and timely maintenance of data related to the project sales and existing/potential customers\n\nSales Support :\n\n- Provide after-sales support to the customers at the project site as required\n\n- Monitor outstanding collections data and escalate to the Project Head Sales for necessary support\n\nOthers :\n\n- Submit Daily Sales Report (DSR) reports and other required data and reports in a timely manner for sales tracking\n\n- Support effective implementation of marketing initiatives to drive sales for the project\n\n- Provide the necessary data to ensure timely payment of brokerage/incentives to Channel Partners\n\n- Ensure timely login of sales as per the defined timelines\n\n- Ensure timely & accurate updation of sales related data on the online sales module to enable generation of reports\n\nDevelopmental :\n\n- Keep abreast of developments in the area of work\n\nInternal & External Interactions :\n\nInternal: Regional Head-Marketing & Sales, Regional Marketing Team, Regional Customer Care Team, Regional Finance, Regional Project Management Team, Regional Design Team, Regional Legal Team\n\nExternal: Brokers, Property Consultants, Customers, Corporates & HNI Clients\n\nEducation & Experience Requirement:\n\n- Graduate/MBA Marketing\n\n- 4 to 10 years of relevant experience",
