      "job_apply_link": "https://in.linkedin.com/jobs/view/director-senior-manager-ux-at-fancode-3519196729",
      "job_description": "Design @ FanCode: We have one mission, To redefine / reimagine the way Sports Fans follow and consume their favourite sports events.\n\nWe are at the beginning of our story and growing at an incredible pace.\n\nOur Design team is focused on creating a universal design language that scales across all our user experiences on multiple platforms, with an aim to provide tens of millions of sports fans with a best-in-class user experience.\n\nAn exciting opportunity where you get to experience firsthand how to define a strategic vision of a budding startup, convert that into a tactical execution plan, and drive the execution to deliver results in the real world. In this role, you define the entire UX strategy for the product or feature, in line with the company’s larger vision. You will facilitate an understanding of the larger business context & user needs to define long & short-term design strategies. Rephrase business objectives from the users’ lens and facilitate innovative problem solving with your team. Create sound execution plan for your design strategy to align various teams like business, content, marketing & technology.\n\nYour Role:\n• Define clear problem statements in line with the long-term objectives for the company and user needs.\n• Collaborate with tech, content, Product, operations & marketing teams to create feasible solutions\n• Run workshops, facilitate co-creation and collaborative design thinking & problem-solving in the team\n• Create concepts, long term strategic solutions, service blueprints, design strategy & execution plans\n• Promote design thinking and user-first mindset while balancing viability & feasibility\n• A keen eye for understanding deep underlying user needs & problems through research & defining path ahead\n• Mentor junior designers through sharp constructive feedback & skill identification\n• Be able to zoom out and see holistic customer experience at a macro level & simultaneously zoom in and give UX/UI feedback at a micro level\n\nMust Have:\n• Minimum 6-8 years of UX work experience in designing mobile applications or websites\n• Experience delivering large projects with multi-functional teams like product, content, marketing, technology.\n• Strong understanding of User-Centered Design Process, Design Principles & Systems, content, and data management.\n• Experience driving design thinking, creative problem solving & clear execution plans at an organizational level\n• An impressive portfolio that showcases process-driven user experience & creative problem-solving design skills\n\nGood to Have:\n• Recognised UX / UI certifications.\n• Experience working in an Agile development process.\n• Technical understanding of CMS, databases, SQL or coding is a plus\n• Knowledge of analytics, generate trends & insights from data\n• Passion for sports\n\nDream Sports is India’s leading sports technology company with brands such as Dream11, the world’s largest fantasy sports platform, FanCode, a premier digital sports platform that personalizes content and commerce for all sports fans, DreamSetGo, a sports experiences platform, and DreamPay, a payment solutions provider.\n\nIt has founded the Dream Sports Foundation to help and champion sportspeople and is an active member of the Federation of Indian Fantasy Sports, the nodal body for the Fantasy Sports industry in India.\n\nFounded in 2008 by Harsh Jain and Bhavit Sheth, Dream Sports is always working on its mission to ‘Make Sports Better’ and is located in Mumbai. Dream Sports has been featured as a ‘Great Places to Work’ by the Great Place to Work’ Institute for four consecutive years. It is also the only sports tech company among India’s best companies to work for in 2021.\n\nFor more information: https://dreamsports.group/\n\nAbout FanCode:\n\nFanCode is India’s premier digital sports destination committed to giving all fans a highly personalised experience across Content, Community and Commerce.\n\nFounded by sports industry veterans Yannick Colaco and Prasana Krishnan in March 2019, FanCode offers interactive live streaming, sports fan merchandise (FanCode Shop), fast interactive live match scores, in-depth live commentary, fantasy sports data and statistics (Fantasy Research Hub), expert fantasy tips, sports news and much more.\n\nFanCode has partnered with both domestic and international sports leagues and associations across multiple sports such as three of the top American Leagues - MLB, NFL, and NBA, FIVB, West Indies Cricket Board, Bangladesh Premier League, Caribbean Premier League, Bundesliga and I-League.\n\nFanCode has already amassed over 27 million+ app installs and won the “Best Sports Startup” award at FICCI India Sports Awards 2019.\n\nGet the FanCode App: iOS | Android\n\nWebsite: www.fancode.com\n\nFanCode Shop: www.shop.fancode.com",
