      "job_description": "Title: Associate Manager/Manager/Senior Manager, Sustainalytics, a Morningstar company\n\n \n\nLocation: Vashi, Navi Mumbai\n\nCompany: Morningstar is a leading provider of independent investment research in North America, Europe, Australia, and Asia. We offer a wide variety of products and solutions that serve market participants of all kinds, including individual and institutional investors in public and private capital markets, financial advisors, asset managers, retirement plan providers and sponsors, and issuers of securities.\n\nBusiness Unit: Sustainalytics provides high-quality, analytical environmental, social and governance (ESG) research, ratings and data to institutional investors and companies that help them identify, understand and manage ESG-driven risks and opportunities. Our mission is to provide the insights required to make more informed decisions that lead to a more just and sustainable global economy.\n\nTeam: The ESG Research team is responsible for producing high quality research content, while continuously developing new research products. The Impact Pillar focuses on capturing companies with involvement in products and services that are considered to have a negative or positive impact, from an ethical and/or sustainability perspective. The team delivers a suite of strategically important ESG research and data products, helping clients comply with regulations such as the EU Taxonomy and Sustainable Finance Disclosure Regulation.\n\nRole: The Research Manager will manage the day-to-day research activities for a team of analysts focused on impact research. The Manager leads a group of team leads and works with internal partners to meet agreed-upon research commitments. The role is responsible for the team's delivery of high-quality and timely research that meets product requirements. The person will be accountable for ensuring and improving the team's performance, productivity, and efficiency.\n\nResponsibilities:\n• People Management\n• Build and lead a team of analysts by providing clear direction, establishing SMART goals, and optimizing resource allocation\n• Stimulate team members to enhance their understanding of relevant ESG impact related aspects and to improve analyst guidance on related research indicators\n• Coach and train team leads/senior analysts to develop the necessary managerial and leadership skills, technical competence, and content expertise\n• Effectively motivate and reward the team and their team leads for maintaining and raising morale\n• Research Output Management\n• Lead effective research planning, analyze team performance, and produce monthly reports for senior management\n• Ensure timely delivery of research, meeting varied research requirements\n• Business Process Improvement\n• Use LEAN Six Sigma and such approaches to improve the research process continuously\n• Map and document processes in SOPs\n• Perform issue management and conduct root cause analysis for reported issues\n\nQualifications:\n• Master’s degree in any discipline\n• 7+ years of relevant work experience, preferably in secondary research/data operations. Experience with ESG/sustainability will be a plus\n• A few years of experience in coaching team leads/senior analysts in team management roles\n• Prior experience in hiring research analysts, setting up research teams, overseeing research activities, improving research processes, and delivering research\n• Ability to work in a fast-paced, international, and technical environment\n• Strong analytical, entrepreneurial, and problem-solving skills\n• Meticulous attention to detail and ability to proactively identify and manage risks\n• Ability to effectively communicate with local and international stakeholders at all levels and form strong relationships\n• Strong project management and execution skills and proven experience optimizing processes\n• Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, Power BI, and PowerPoint\n• Affinity with text mining/artificial intelligence is an asset\n• Alignment with Sustainalytics’ mission, vision, and values\n\nMorningstar is an equal opportunity employer.\n\nAbout Us\n\nSustainalytics is a Morningstar company dedicated to responsible investment with over 25 years' experience in ESG research and ratings. With an extensive client base across asset managers, asset owners and investment banks, our mission is to provide the insights required for investors and companies to make more informed decisions that lead to a more just and sustainable global economy.\n\nAs Morningstar’s ESG center of excellence we are responsible for driving both the commercial success and innovation of its ESG products as well as its overall ESG strategy.\n\nIn these times, we rely on virtual team meetings and management practices, as well as a remote buddy program, to support a smooth integration in our virtual offices. New team members are onboarded and start their first day with the company from the safety of their homes.\n\nFor more information, visit www.sustainalytics.com",
