      "job_description": "We at Skechers India , are hiring for the position of Senior Manager - Process Excellence and Audits to be based at our New Distribution Centre, Taloja.\n\nPlease find below job details :\n\nPosition: Senior Manager - Process Excellence and Audits\n\nDepartment : Supply Chain & Logistics\n\nLocation : Taloja\n\nEducation : Ideal candidate: Industrial Engineering graduate with Six-sigma certification from reputed college, preferably NITIE, VJTI or 10 to 12 Years experience in Business Excellence\n\nExperience :\n\n- Supply Chain professional with 7-8 years of exposure to warehouse operations, Business excellence, Project life cycle management, contracting & project planning.\n\n- Experience of building a large DC from concept to Go-Live.\n\n- Experience from Automotive, Large 3PL organizations and e-commerce background who has exposure to smart warehousing process improvement and audits will be preferred.\n\nJob Description :\n\n- Be part of Setting-up & Core Team Managing and driving operations excellence and continuous improvement projects\n\n- Process implementation, Change Management, Conduct KPI performance trend analysis\n\n- Design and ensure successful implementation of business/ operations\n\n- Energize teams and stakeholders, collect data, conduct diagnostic analysis, identify opportunities that positively impact quality, cost, delivery excellence, and customer satisfaction, and present action plan to management\n\n- Select and implement need based and appropriate quality tools such as TQM, Quality Circles, Kaizen, 5-S, problem solving, statistical techniques and several other tools for continuous improvement.\n\n- Create the necessary governance and review mechanisms to drive transactional quality\n\n- Conduct KPI performance trend analysis, identify quality improvement opportunities, and drive improvement initiatives using the appropriate quality tools\n\n- Identify opportunities for Quality Improvement projects; create a pipeline of improvement projects; provide necessary coaching and guidance to run these projects to deliver value additions.\n\n- Process Re-Engineering to drive operations centricity, efficiency, effectiveness, agility & reliability in SCM.\n\n- Identification & Resolution of key Business Challenges and enabling teams to address & manage the challenges to achieve Customer Satisfaction and Cost Optimization to maximize profit .\n\n- Establishing & managing corporate infrastructure for Business Excellence which includes team capability\n\n- Continuously improve existing process and help teams design new processes that are robust, effective, and efficient\n\n- Managing Organization wide Training & Development of Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt, Green Belt, Black Belt\n\n- Identify key Business Challenges and enabling teams to address & manage the challenges to achieve Customer Satisfaction, Profit Maximization & Cost Optimization.\n\n- Stake Holders & Change Management to deploy To-Be efficient & Complaint Processes in all domains.\n\n- Lead & mentor project teams thereby creating a value proposition for businesses through improved return on Investment.\n\nCore Competencies\n\n- Supply Chain Management, Six Sigma Black Belt, Warehouse Operations, Process analysis, adaptability to new systems understanding of specifications of warehouse equipments, storage Infra, electricals, Warehouse & Engineering layouts.\n\n- Continuous process and quality improvement systems, design, develop and implement performance measuring reporting, Design SOPs, and process audits.\n\n- Lead improvement initiatives by enlisting and influencing cross-functional teams that deliver tangible business results through the application of Lean and Six Sigma principles, methodologies and tools.\n\nSkill Sets\n\n- Supply Chain Orientation, warehouse operations, process, infrastructure specifications and understanding\n\n- Provide thoughtful leadership and advice to management on process improvement and in developing transformational business cases\n\n- Know-how of process mapping, process analysis, and detailed operations understating\n\n- Gap analysis, designing SOPs, as-is and to-be\n\n- Experience in capacity building templates for performance measuring reporting, and continuous improvement systems with good exposure to automation, WMS, TMS warehouse operations\n\n- Excellent communication skills (oral and written) in Marathi, Hindi and English, as well as a strong credibility and integrity in this domain",
