      "job_description": "Department Profile\n\nFrom global institutions to hedge funds, investors come to Morgan Stanley for sales, trading, and market-making services in almost every type of financial instrument in all the world's financial markets. Morgan Stanley professionals use our network and technology to provide liquidity and sophisticated analysis, to manage risk and execute reliably in the fast-changing markets.\n\nMorgan Stanley's Institutional Equity Division (IED) is a world leader in the origination, distribution and trading of equity, equity-linked and equity-derivative securities. Our broad and deep client relationships, market-leading platform and intellectual insights enable us to be a world-class service provider to our clients for their financing, market access and portfolio management needs.\n\nGlobal Markets Group is the offshoring arm of Morgan Stanley's Equity businesses in India. It covers functions across IED ranging from those associated with sales, trading, analytics, strats to risk management.\n\nPrimary Responsibilities\n\nDescription\n\nMorgan Stanley Research is seeking an application support Analyst to join our ISG data Management team to help manage quantitative data products through a global application platform. The candidate will work closely with various teams including subject matter experts to assist in client onboarding/entitlement and level 1 support. The candidate will also coordinate with technology and cross-divisional data teams to help identify root cause for client issues\n\nJob responsibilities\n• Onboarding, entitlement and product support for clients and internal users of data products\n• Setup and verify client data feeds\n• Communicate with client for onboarding, delivery & FAQs.\n• Coordinate with technology teams to design, construct, install, test and maintain data management systems\n• Capture, investigate, triage and coordinate w/ internal teams for resolution of client data inquiries and incidents\n• Monitor active data pipelines / run data quality monitors\n• Perform daily manual data cleaning, verification activities\n• Help create and evolve data standards and product documentation\n• Track data requests and run periodic reporting\n• Work will happen in different shifts as this will be for global support\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\nSkills required (essential)\n\nTechnical Qualifications\n• Experience with using data profiling tools to query data, identify anomalies, gaps and issues\n• Experience working with data in various forms: files (Excel, csv...), relational databases, data warehouses, unstructured data environments (HIVE, Impala)\n• General awareness of data management best practices, emerging trends, and challenges\n• Experience and/or exposure to financial data; experience with datasets commonly used in investment Research analysis (both macro and Equity) preferred\n\nRequired\n• Bachelor's Degree/MBA from an accredited higher learning institution required or equivalent combination of experience and education\n• 7+ years' experience in financial services/Application support role\n• Strong analytical and reasoning skills; able to decompose complex problems and projects into manageable pieces; comfortable suggesting and presenting solutions\n• Comfortable working in a large organization and interfacing with a broad set of stakeholders across various functions (i.e., Business, IT, Operations)\n• Excellent verbal and written communication skills presenting complex analytical results to both technical and non-technical audiences",
