      "job_apply_link": "https://angel.co/company/raise-financial/jobs/1789904-manager-senior-manager-partnerships-alliances",
      "job_description": "Role Summary: Raise is built on this core philosophy - we will bring exceptionally great products, awesome user experience and best in class customer service to our users. We have started with our first step by launching Investment & Trading platform – Dhan (www.dhan.co)\n\nNow it is time for us to expand our business and partner with like mind organizations – banks, large fintechs and financial services companies (BFSI sector) to provide exceptionally good products & customer experience for their users.\n\nThe Growth & Partnerships team is the first point of contact a new potential partner for Dhan and will be responsible from pitch to product rollout experience for them. You will be the single point contact for Business and will lead and manage relationship, account, business and its growth.\n\nAs a part of the team at Raise, you will identify new business opportunities in order to generate revenue, improve profitability and help the business expand and grow. Self-motivated, result-oriented, and a natural tendency of pushing one’s limits by spotting creative and unique ways of selling are some of the must-haves for this role.\n\nPrior experience in a similar role is must, and also experience in working with industry leaders, interaction and partnerships with Top Management, CXOs and Senior Executives in Financial Services, Banks, Fintech is a must.\n\nIf you are someone who is passionate about Financial Services and Fintech products in India wherein you feel the clients / customers should get the best possible experience, then you are looking at the place where you should apply. This would require you to be excited about the business and work with all stakeholders to drive excellence.\n\nExpected Responsibilities:\n• To research and identify new business opportunities, including new markets, growth areas, trends, clients, alliances, partnerships, products and services and often seek new ways of reaching existing markets\n• To generate revenue leads and connect prospective partners to drive in more revenues\n• To foster and develop relationships with new clients while maintaining an excellent rapport with the existing ones.\n• To understand the needs of the partners and be able to respond effectively with a plan of execution on how to meet these\n• To think strategically by seeing the bigger picture and setting aims and objectives in order to develop and improve the business\n• To have a thorough knowledge and understanding of businesses products or services and be able to advise clients / others about them\n• To closely and collaboratively work with the product, growth and marketing teams in order to provide the best and feasible solutions to the partners.\n• To keep up with the trends and changes in the financial area of business, especially the investment sector and Indian markets.\n• To carry out timely sales forecasts and analysis and present findings to senior management\n\nExpected Skills:\n\nWe are a start-up and we are focusing on fast growth with quality products hence the ability to work in a fast-paced environment goes without saying. Other than that:\n• Master’s in Business Administration from Tier II institute would be preferred.\n• 5-8 years of work experience with at least 4-5 years of experience working in a similar role\n• Exceptionally well written and verbal communication skills that are needed for communicating with a range of people both internally and externally is a must have\n• Excellent presentation and negotiation skills with innate poise and confidence\n• Tenacity and drive to seek new business and meet or exceed revenue targets\n• Strong interpersonal skills for building and developing great client relationships\n• A sound ability to understand sales performance and take effective measures to further improvise\n• Result oriented and collaborative approach with a laser focus for clients\n• Self-starter, high on initiative and confidence to start things from scratch\n• Work experience in a business where you witnessed and were involved in product scaling from zero to 1 is great!\n• Past and latest experience with a financial services company will be awesome. Banking, financial service, or payment services companies are super!\n\nRaise focuses on Payments, Insurance, Consumer Lending, and Wealth Management. Their company has offices in Mumbai. They have a mid-size team that's between 51-200 employees.\n\nYou can view their website at https://raiseholding.co/ or find them on Twitter and LinkedIn.",
