      "job_description": "Job Summary:\n\nDrip Capital is looking for a skilled SDR manager/Preslaes Manager to lead our USA team. The ideal applicant will be in charge of overseeing a group of Sales Development Representatives (SDRs) and directing the pre-sales procedure by generating leads, identifying potential clients, and working with the sales team to meet revenue targets.\n\nSDRs are in charge of identifying and qualifying leads through outbound prospecting, inbound lead qualification, and other lead generation activities. They are frequently the first point of contact for prospective customers. The candidate is in charge of making sure that his team generates leads efficiently and qualifies them for the sales team to close. In order to achieve alignment and success, this involves establishing and monitoring performance metrics, coaching and training team members, and close collaboration with other departments.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n2. Working in the night typically from 7 pm to 3 am IST\n4. Manage and lead the SDR team, providing coaching and guidance to ensure team members meet and exceed their targets\n6. Collaborate with the sales team to develop and execute targeted sales campaigns and strategies\n8. Conduct market research to identify potential clients and generate leads\n10. Utilize sales tools and technology to maximize productivity and efficiency, such as HubSpot, Outreach/MailChimp, PhoneBurner, ChatGpt, ZoomInfo, Sales Navigator, QuillBot,and TrippleSession.\n12. Evaluate the effectiveness of the pre-sales process and identify areas for improvement\n14. Monitor and analyze pre-sales metrics and KPIs to track performance and identify opportunities for growth\n16. Develop and maintain relationships with key stakeholders, including sales, marketing, and product teams\n18. Manage the pre-sales budget, including forecasting and reporting\n\nQualifications:\n\n2. Bachelor's degree in business, marketing, or a related field\n4. 4+ years of experience in leading pre-sales or SDR management for a US business/market, preferably in the financial or fintech industry\n6. Strong expertise in outbound sales, primarily through email, phone, and social selling\n8. A proven track record of delivering sales pipeline at a fast growing company with multiple sales segments with an inbound and outbound model\n10. You are an expert at partnering with marketing to plan and execute multi-touch, multi-channel campaigns\n12. Strong leadership and coaching skills, with a proven track record of attracting, retaining, and motivating exceptional team members\n14. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively across departments and with clients\n16. Analytical mindset, with the ability to use data to drive decisions and measure performance\n18. You are an expert at prospecting via Linkedin, Outreach, SalesNav, Zoominfo, HubSpot, PhoneBurner, ChatGpt, ZoomInfo, Sales Navigator, QuillBot,and TrippleSession\n20. Proactive, solution and results-driven attitude, with a focus on achieving and exceeding revenue targets\n22. Ability to work in a fast-paced and dynamic environment\n\nIf you feel you meet the qualifications and requirements listed above, we encourage you to apply for the role of SDR Manager/Preslaes Manager for our USA team.",
