      "job_description": "Role: Principal – Wealth Management\n\nLocation: Mumbai/Bangalore\n\nGrade: G\n\nRole of Principal in the Mercer Wealth India Pvt Ltd.\n\nWe will count on you to:\n\nAs part of its growth plans in India, Mercer is setting up a wealth management practice in India that will offer Ultra High Net Worth Individuals and Families, an array of wealth management services in both the distribution and advisory spaces. These services are platformed on Mercer’s globally renowned research and our commitment to be client-centric in our offering.\n\nMercer is looking for an entrepreneurial minded leaders in Bangalore and Mumbai to lead the private wealth business in the respective locations.\n\nWhat is in it for you\n\nSet up phase\n• Work closely with India Business leader in various actions related to the setup of the wealth management practice of Mercer.\n• Hire a team of Relationship Managers that will report to the candidate in Bangalore/Mumbai with appropriate clientele.\n• Contribute to various workstreams such as marketing, research, products, operations, technology by providing inputs to the functional leaders of the same.\n\nOn-going\n• Responsible for revenue and profitability of the wealth management desk in the Bangalore/West region.\n• Lead and provide oversight to a team of Relationship Managers that work closely with clients in offering wealth management solutions of Mercer\n• Evolve strategies and solutions that can drive growth in the wealth management segment\n• Engage and maintain relationships with key clients\n• Contribute to various workstreams such as marketing, research, products, operations, technology by providing inputs to the functional leaders of the same.\n• Maintain and manage a book of existing client relationships\n• Work within ambit of Mercer processes and guidelines\n\nWhat you need to have:\n• Minimum 15 Years’ experience in Wealth Management space, selling investment services, products to UHNIs and Family Offices\n• Exposure and understanding of investment products\n• Managed growth focused teams preferably in the financial services space (with further preference to services to UHNI and Family Office clientele)\n\nWhat makes you stand out:\n• Ability to manage a team of client focused relationship managers\n• Willingness to think and act entrepreneurially\n• Decision making skills with strong sense of ownership\n• Willingness to be part of a client focused long term play in the Wealth space\n• Ability to manage relationships across various segments of stakeholders\n\nMercer believes in building brighter futures by redefining the world of work, reshaping retirement and investment outcomes, and unlocking real health and well-being. Mercer’s more than 25,000 employees are based in 44 countries and the firm operates in over 130 countries. Mercer is a business of Marsh & McLennan (NYSE: MMC), the world’s leading professional services firm in the areas of risk, strategy and people, with 76,000 colleagues and annual revenue of $17 billion. Through its market-leading businesses including Marsh, Guy Carpenter and Oliver Wyman, Marsh & McLennan helps clients navigate an increasingly dynamic and complex environment. For more information, visit https://www.me.mercer.com/. Follow Mercer on Twitter @Mercer.",
