      "job_description": "Morgan Stanley's Institutional Securities Group (ISG) is a remarkably broad and diversified business. We provide institutions with almost every kind of financial product and service across the world's major markets. Whether you're interested in planning complex deals; trading on the moment-to-moment movements of the capital markets; analysing the financial needs of a company or a wealthy family, Morgan Stanley is the place to be.\n\nThe Fixed Income Division is comprised of Interest Rate and Currency Products, Credit Products and Distribution. Professionals in the Division assess and actively manage risk, trade securities, and structure as well as execute innovative transactions in the fast-paced and constantly changing global markets. The Commodities Division is a market leader in energy, metals, and agricultural product trading worldwide whose professional’s trade in both physical and derivative commodity risk.\n\nGlobal Markets Group is the offshoring arm of Morgan Stanley’s Sales & Trading businesses in India. It covers functions across FID and Institutional Equities Division (IED) ranging from those associated with sales, trading, analytics, strats to risk management.\n\nPrimary Responsibilities\n\nThe role is based out of Mumbai and requires working with the Japan Fixed Income Sales Team. The role will require a fast-learning, dynamic, pro-active and self-motivated person to assist the team in day-to-day activities.\n\nThe desk covers Global fund clients and Japanese domestic financial institutions across a large set of products in the Fixed Income space:\n• JPY Swaps/Swaptions/Cross-Currency Basis Swaps/Bond Options trades.\n• JGB cash/Repo trades.\n• Non-JPY governments cash/swap/repo trades\n• Other bonds/CDS trades.\n• The pace of the desk demands that you complete each task promptly with a high degree of accuracy. Also, the ability to organize your time and complete each task on time will be a key factor in determining your suitability for the role\n\nJob Description\n• Capture the trades of Fixed Income and Derivatives, and confirm the accuracy of sales trade bookings\n• Prepare the preliminary confirmations for derivative trade such as Bond options on behalf of Sales.\n• Work with Sales and Operations for the quick resolution of trade/settlement related issues.\n• Maintenance of propriety databases and input the data such as trade details and clients.\n• Help preparing presentations for internal/external meetings\n• Other ad-hoc tasks including administrative tasks in order to support Tokyo FID activities\n\nSkills required (essential)\n• 3+ year experience in FID business/operations with basic knowledge of Fixed Income and Derivative products would be preferable\n• Excellent communication skills both verbal and written\n• Ability to multi-task\n• High degree of attention to detail\n• Strong analytical skills\n• Ability to multi-task\n• Proactiveness towards learning and executing tasks\n• Fluency in Japanese language would be preferred\n• Work timing: 5.30am IST to 2.30pm IST (negotiable)\n\nMorgan Stanley is an equal opportunities employer. We work to provide a supportive and inclusive environment where all individuals can maximize their full potential.",
