      "job_description": "About our client:\n\nOur Client operates in the Packaged Foods Industry, with its headquarters rooted strongly in the United States. It has its branches spread to more than 180 countries. They fall under the Fortune 500 Companies. Their core business is manufacturing and selling a broad range of convenience foods. It also is a well passed down legacy business, making a mark through history.\n\nOverview:\n• The Senior Manager, Global HRIS leads and develops a global team of HRIS professionals.\n• They will ensure services are delivered per Service Level Agreements (SLAs), projects are completed timely and the end-user experience is prioritized.\n\nResponsibilities:\n• Manage day-to-day delivery operations of HRIS.\n• Select, train and develop HRIS delivery team.\n• Work closely with HRIS COE to ensure compliance.\n• Provides the necessary training to meet end users needs.\n• Develops, implements, and modifies software & hardware requirements based on business requirements.\n• Work with business and vendors to identify system solutions to support business priorities and improved user experience.\n• Ensure system controls are in place and appropriately supported (per 404 SOX requirements).\n• Deliver financial commitments (annual budget and savings targets).\n• People Management: Manages a team of three Global HRIS Regional Managers, six Business Analysts, and two Associates directly that include Position Data Management manager.\n• Leads Global HRIS strategy through CoE collaboration. Responsible for Managers development, Training, coaching & establishing SLA’s & KPI’s for HRIS delivery.\n• HR Systems: Accountable for Global HR applications and systems including core HR, compensation, Application Tracking Systems, Performance, Role based security, Case Management, Reporting and analytics, payroll and time & attendance integrations.\n• Evaluates and recommends HR systems and solutions, articulates the business case including cost analysis, ensure alignment with stakeholders and drive successful implementation and administration.\n• Represents HRIS Change Control and governance board to lead change management & approvals for new projects and enhancements for HRIS.\n• Data Integrity: Establish HR data audit protocols with guidance from Internal Audit, and ensure that on-going audits of HR data in myHR occur on routine schedule.\n• Reporting & Analysis: Assess needs, recommend, develop, prepare, and continuously improve HR reports and analytics to facilitate effective decision-making.\n• Drives overall HRIS Program Management that span approximately 200 projects, 140 enhancements from start to finish on a year-to-year basis.\n• Leads HRO & Tier1 team by providing directions and training & development that involve QRG’s/DTP’s for system processes.\n\nRequirements:\n• Bachelor’s Degree in IT, Human Resources or Management preferred.\n• 10+ years of work experience within in HRIS, HR, IT or Finance.\n• 10+ years of experience with Success Factors, SAP HR, Workday or equivalent.\n• 2-5 years project management experience with demonstrated success in leading people and projects.\n• Very Advanced Excel skills, including vbasic, macros, data slicers and advanced formulation.\n• Must be detail conscious and have strong analytical skills.\n\nWorking Relationship:\n• Reports to: Hire To Retire (HTR) Global Process Delivery Lead (GBS).\n• Supervises to: Direct reports - 3 Managers & 5 Business Analysts.\n• Peer Relationships: Works closely with HRIS COE, Global and Region HTR leads and HRO Team.\n• Key contacts (Internal & External): Business Leaders, COEs, IT, HRDs and Vendors.\n\nWork Environment:\n• Work is performed in an open office setting.\n• As a global role, Senior Manager, HRIS is expected to be available as needed to manage a “follow the sun” team schedule.\n• Role requires travel up to 15% to Romania, Mexico, India and US.\n\nDimension:\n• Performance will be evaluated at the individual and team level based on selected metrics and identified goals.\n• Works in close partnership with Information Technology team.\n• Leads 16-20 global professionals across all regions.",
