      "job_description": "Brand / Sr Brand Mgr - E commerce\n\n- Leading e commerce market place requires Senior Manager ( E commerce Marketing)- Mumbai\n\n- One of our client a leading e market place with 14+ years of expertise in e-commerce, we nurture your brand to grow. Our AI-powered solution allows for quick scale-up of your brand and equips it to serve a global audience efficiently. With our 'Cost-Efficient Execution' model, we have set more than 2,500 brands on their growth path through our more than 125 marketplaces spread across the continents. We used our streamlined systems and processes to ensure flawless transactions from anywhere across the globe. We aim to deliver an outstanding customer experience and, in the process, amplify the value of our partnerships.\n\n- We are looking for Manager/Senior Manager -Brand Marketing ( E commerce )for our client's office for Mumbai /Bangalore/ Gurgaon location.\n\nDesignation : Senior Manager( E commerce marketing)\n\nCompany : E-commerce market place\n\nLocation : Mumbai, India\n\nJob Type : Full-Time\n\nAbout us :\n\n- Founded in 2007, E-commerce company with a global reach of more than 120 countries and over 100 marketplaces.\n\n- We have catered to over 5 million customers worldwide in a short amount of time. Currently, we have 21 curated websites that bring to our customers. We are a Houston, Texas-based S- corporation and have been in the business for almost 13 years. We have a dedicated and strong team of 650+ associates and we are continuously adding new people to our team. It is consistently ranked among the top online shopping destinations as we have been rated as the Top 100 Sellers- on Amazon, and Top 50 in Walmart, and have also managed to achieve the number 1 ranking on eBay.\n\nAbout the role :\n\n- The ideal candidate must be able to think and act both strategically and tactically, be an innovative leader who is an effective communicator, capable of handling multiple projects and thrives in ambiguity and strong communication skills.\n\nResponsibilities include :\n\n- Own projects with considerable scope and/or complexity with significant impact on customer experience and Amazon's business\n\n- Work with cross functional teams and internal teams, including technology teams, to define, drive, and launch improvements to the shopping experience.\n\n- Own creation of marketing program, and multiple key traffic drivers, to acquire new customers.\n\n- Develop, test, and execute an aggressive multi-channel marketing plans to drive customer acquisition and authority.\n\n- Develop the category's editorial direction, style guidelines, merchandising calendar, promotions, and coop packages.\n\n- Understand and use merchandising along with customer facing metrics to guide decision making.\n\n- Present to senior management externally and internally.\n\n- Work with external agencies and inputs from other sources to build authoritative content for the site.\n\nBasic Qualifications :\n\n- MBA Preferred\n\n- 4+ years of experience in marketing (Preferable Fashion/Beauty), editorial and visual merchandising.\n\n- Experience with project leadership requiring coordination of cross-team resources and persistence to accomplish goals\n\n- Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects prioritization, planning and task delegation\n\nPreferred Qualifications :\n\n- Brand Management\n\n- Knowledge of Fashion/Beauty Trends\n\n- Knowledge of xml\n\n- Blogger\n\nInternal Job Description :\n\n- The ideal candidate must be able to think and act both strategically and tactically, be an innovative leader who is an effective communicator, capable of handling multiple projects and thrives in ambiguity and strong communication skills.\n\nResponsibilities include :\n\n- Own projects with considerable scope and/or complexity with significant impact on customer experience and Amazon's business\n\n- Work with cross functional teams and internal teams, including technology teams, to define, drive, and launch improvements to the shopping experience.\n\n- Own creation of marketing program, and multiple key traffic drivers, to acquire new customers.\n\n- Develop, test, and execute an aggressive multi-channel marketing plans to drive customer acquisition and authority.\n\n- Develop the category's editorial direction, style guidelines, merchandising calendar, promotions, and coop packages.\n\n- Understand and use merchandising along with customer facing metrics to guide decision making.\n\n- Present to senior management externally and internally.\n\n- Work with external agencies and inputs from other sources to build authoritative content for the site.\n\nQualifications and Skills :\n\n- Bachelor's degree in Mktg Business, Marketing,\n\n- 4+ years of experience in product management, marketing, or an analytical function, preferably at a start-up or other fast-paced environment.\n\n- 4+ years of e-commerce experience, preferably working within the Amazon ecosystem/Amazon marketing.\n\n- Ability to dig through data, draw conclusions and make recommendations.\n\n- Excellent written and verbal communication skills, a high level of organization, and impeccable attention to detail.\n\n- Ability to handle aggressive deadlines and prioritize work in a fast-paced, often ambiguous environment with fire drills coming up on a near-daily basis.\n\n- A highly analytical self-starter who can manage multiple projects and figure out complex problems without a lot of oversight.\n\n- Demonstrated ability to create engaging content, come up with creative ideas, and think outside the box.\n\n- Positive attitude, reliable, transparent and enjoy working with different types of people.\n\n- Strong proficiency in excel.\n\n- Preferably MBA, PG in Marketing, Advertising, and Communication\n\n- If the position interests you and you find a fitment kindly share your cv\n\nContact :\n\nPranav : 7011354635\n\nKindly share :\n\n- Current CTC and notice period\n- Expected CTC\n- Open to work in Mumbai\n- Relevant experience in e commerce domain\n- Exposure in US mkt and Amazon marketing",
