      "job_description": "About Practo : https://www.practo.com/\n\nWhat if, instead of a job, you had a mission?\n\nA mission to create the future of healthcare alongside a team of brilliant, passionate people, on a canvas that touches billions of consumers around the world?\n\nIt’s what we do at Practo.\n\nPracto is at the intersection of health and technology. We build products and solutions that impact one of humanity’s most personal aspects – health.\n\nApart from being deeply personal, healthcare is also immensely emotional for all stakeholders. Whether it is our doctor community, the patients, or their respective families. Further, this is an industry that is evolving rapidly while at the same time having considerable regulation.\n\nAre you passionate about making an impact in Healthcare? Do you have the ability to think from first principles & solve complex problems? Would you rate high on an entrepreneurial streak with amazing hustling capabilities? Do you have an instinctive ability to proactively collaborate and work with a lot of different teams and individuals?\n\nAbout The Role\n\nPracto is looking for an Alliances and Partnerships Manager, who will be responsible for identifying and onboarding new channel partners in order to achieve business targets.\n\nThe candidate should have hands-on and direct experience in building brand new alliance partners and driving business outcomes.\n\nLocation: Mumbai/ Delhi NCR.\n\nJob Description\n• Identify, onboard, and close new channel partners that deliver the next level of growth for the Company\n• Actively contribute to the overall achievement of sales and company targets\n• Manage relationships with existing & new channel partners in order to create new opportunities\n• Work with the marketing team to develop plans that support the partner network and generate deal flow\n• Negotiating win-win partnership deals and ensuring mutually beneficial partnership terms that are in line with business objectives and strategy\n• Plan business outcomes and co-own all business metrics and growth for the Partnerships line of business\n• Conceptualize, execute and develop strategic alliances with companies, Insurance players, TPA, and Brokers having a good SME and corporate client base, that will accelerate innovation and revenue growth across a range of products\n• Grow the relationship and revenue potential with these strategic partners and deepen relations with partners by looking at opportunities for upselling and cross-selling.\n• Collaborate with the Sales team on closing new business generated through partnerships\n• Assist in preparing RFP/ RFQs\n• Regularly review and measure partners’ progress to ensure they remain profitable\n• Provide regular reports on KPIs and/or our Strategy\n• Keep up to date and understand competitive products and pricing strategies to ensure or retain and grow market share\n\nDesired Skill Set Required\n• 4 – 7 Years of Previous Channel sales experience, B2B aggregators, digital platforms, partnership roles\n• Have the ability to drive channel lead generation and joint marketing programs\n• Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment as well as in cross-functional teams\n• Have the ability to influence others and connect with clients at various seniority levels\n• A bonus would be experienced with customers aligned to the current business vertical of Corporate Health & Wellness",
