      "job_description": "United Way Mumbai is a part of the 130 year old United Way movement spanning 41 countries across the world. Our mission is to improve lives by mobilizing the caring power of communities to advance the common good.\n\nWe work closely with a network of 400+ NGOs and a large number of corporates for their CSR programmes, workplace giving campaigns and other events. This includes designing of CSR policy and strategies, due diligence of NGO partners, programme implementation, employee volunteering, impact assessments and financial and programmatic reporting.\n\nOver the past 16 years, we have partnered with over 300 companies and over 1,00,000 individual donors investing close to INR 312 crore for community development projects. We work across 6 key focus areas – education, health, income, environment, public safety and social inclusion – in urban and rural communities.\n\nWe are also the philanthropy partners for the Tata Mumbai Marathon- India’s biggest charity platform.\n\nReports To: Chief Operating Officer\n\nJob Overview: The position is responsible for leading and managing the marketing and communication function including all special events and campaigns of United Way of Mumbai. This is a high visibility position requiring strong levels of maturity and intelligence in nurturing and maintaining relationships with a large set of stakeholders.\n\nJob Responsibilities:\n\nCommunications:\n• Develop and lead the organization’s marketing and communications to support fundraising goals.\n• Develop an annual marketing and communications tactical plan, including PR and online marketing.\n• Conceptualize and execute a comprehensive, multi-faceted stakeholder plan that supports the UWM’s strategies and objectives, builds relationships with key audiences, and works to position UWM as the leader in the social impact space.\n• Oversee creative direction and production of all campaign marketing materials, included but not limited to brochure, handouts, website, multimedia (if any) and other supplemental digital communications.\n• Write, edit, and manage publication of communications materials.\n• Educate stakeholders, press, bloggers, sector analysts and influencers about UWM’s core programs and initiatives\n• Scan sector for positioning opportunities, actively profile UWM (and principal UWM contact) in key print, electronic & digital media entities and develop relationships with key stakeholders\n• Handle UWM’s social media presence and engagement.\n• Prepare content and compile reports for external communications like website, newsletters, sector reports and presentations.\n• Handle the communications and promotional requirements of the Tata Mumbai Marathon among the stakeholders – NGO’s, corporate, individuals.\n\nCampaigns:\n\nThe predominant event is the Tata Mumbai Marathon (TMM). The TMM is India’s biggest charity event, annually raising Rs 46 Crores for nearly 300 NGOs with participation from hundreds of companies, fundraisers and thousands of donors. United Way of Mumbai is the philanthropy partner of the event and serves as the philanthropic exchange connecting donors to charities by creating and implementing an organized and structured charity platform and process.\n\nThis position works closely with all participating NGOs to build their capacities to help them leverage the fundraising platform provided. Create, improve and communicate the charity structure to maximize the fund raising capacity and visibility of all participating charities via the event.\n• Lead the campaigns team Maintain excellent processes to ensure flawless execution of the charity structure.\n• Manage the entire funds cycle- raising, receiving, accounting, reconciling, disbursing and reporting.\n• Create and implement a communication strategy to leverage the visibility of the charity aspect of the TMM and various campaigns\n• Conceptualize, lead and run various online campaigns.\n• Manage and develop relationships with NGOs, Corporate, Fundraisers, Donors, vendors and partners.\n• Lead and manage the special events team and improve team efficiency.\n\nProfile Requisites\n• 8+ years’ of work experience\n• Master’s degree in Mass media/Marketing/Journalism preferred\n• Organized and an excellent communicator- written, oral and presentational.\n• A people’s person with natural flair for developing relationships and network.\n• Excellent with MS office especially with MS Excel. Familiarity and comfort using creative process software\n• Creative and innovative thinker. Problem solver. Solution oriented.\n• Have passion and drive to make a difference in society through supporting causes.\n• Great understanding of social and traditional media and comfortable with the use of technology to improve the effectiveness of the platform.\n• Have demonstrable experience handling large and complex activities/events/processes.\n• An understanding of the non profit sector is desirable but not essential. Sensitivity to the sector is essential.\n\nRemuneration: Subject to relevant qualification, experience & merit; the salary range is 17 to 20 LPA.\n\nIf you think you might be suitable, apply now and we’ll reach out to you soon.",
